WEBVTT

00:02.082 --> 00:06.407
The Jerusalem channel is made with the support of you, our viewers.

00:07.128 --> 00:08.269
Thank you for watching.

00:12.233 --> 00:18.640
Holding profound significance for believers in the risen Lord Jesus is the concept of the rapture.

00:19.281 --> 00:27.410
The glorious moment when both deceased believers and those of us who are still alive will be subtly snatched up to the Lord in the air.

00:27.970 --> 00:34.740
This imminent event is vividly described in the Bible in 1 Thessalonians 4, 16 and 17.

00:35.661 --> 00:45.755
For the Lord Himself will descend from heaven with a shout, with a voice of the archangel, and with the sound of the trumpet of God, and the dead in Christ will rise first.

00:46.356 --> 00:56.050
Then we who are alive and remain will be caught up together with them in the clouds to meet the Lord in the air, and so will always be with the Lord.

00:56.674 --> 01:01.182
Many professing believers, unfortunately, scoff at the pre-tribulational rapture.

01:01.944 --> 01:05.730
But there's a remnant who anticipate this imminent event.

01:05.750 --> 01:12.442
And for us, it's essential to be spiritually prepared and also to guard our physical and mental health.

01:13.264 --> 01:18.834
I'm preaching first to myself today, but I hope you'll also be blessed by my thoughts.

01:30.274 --> 01:32.036
Shalom, I'm Christine Dark.

01:32.056 --> 01:36.542
The catching up or rapture is alluded to in the New Testament as a mystery.

01:37.243 --> 01:43.471
Paul wrote to believers in 1 Thessalonians 15, behold, I'm going to tell you a mystery.

01:44.212 --> 01:46.836
We're not all going to die, but we'll all be changed.

01:46.936 --> 01:57.650
In a moment, he said, in the twinkling of an eye, at the last trump, for the trumpet will sound and the dead will be raised incorruptible, and we shall be changed.

01:58.530 --> 02:08.704
After experiencing many dreams about this glorious event called the Rapture, it's always been my art and hope to be alive when Jesus comes to snatch away his bride.

02:09.305 --> 02:13.791
And indeed, we're surrounded by all the signs that he is coming soon.

02:13.851 --> 02:24.466
By doing our best to maintain our health, we will position ourselves to live fully in service to God until that glorious day suddenly arrives.

02:25.314 --> 02:34.243
The scripture is emphasized that our bodies are temples of the Holy Spirit, and that obedience to God brings blessings of well-being and mental health.

02:35.264 --> 02:39.528
Of course, a foundational aspect of physical health is proper nutrition.

02:40.669 --> 02:48.417
This Bible encourages us to view food as a blessing from God, but it also warns against gluttony and excess.

02:49.418 --> 02:53.202
We have to make a conscious effort to practice portion control

02:53.698 --> 02:58.926
and to avoid processed foods, high in sugar, and artificial additives as well.

03:00.068 --> 03:10.565
A number of Bible-based diet books extol Mediterranean-style whole foods such as the What Would Jesus Eat Cookbook.

03:10.585 --> 03:21.522
In it, Dr. Don Colbert examined what Jesus would have eaten based upon Bible foods such as olive oil, whole grains, fish, honey, fruits, and vegetables.

03:22.658 --> 03:33.128
Evangelist Ray Comfort has published the ultimate health foods, nine foods Jesus ate or recommended, tying them to modern health benefits.

03:33.929 --> 03:44.719
He listed honey, butter, not margarine, fish, lamb, beef, or veal as in the fatted calf, salt, eggs, figs, bread, and chicken.

03:45.920 --> 03:51.666
Hydration, of course, is equally important to drink plenty of water to support bodily functions.

03:52.578 --> 03:59.745
The Bible reminds us that exercise and healthy eating honor God and hopefully will sustain us until the trumpet sounds.

04:00.726 --> 04:04.410
Scripture reinforces the link between obedience and health.

04:05.611 --> 04:09.475
Exodus 23, 25 is a key verse.

04:09.495 --> 04:13.398
You shall serve the Lord your God and He will bless your bread and your water.

04:14.219 --> 04:17.322
And then He promises to take away sickness from among you.

04:18.163 --> 04:21.106
Additionally, in Exodus 15, 26,

04:21.570 --> 04:39.576
God said, if you will diligently listen to the voice of the Lord your God and do that which is right in his eyes and give ear to his commandments and keep all of his statutes, then he said, I will put none of the diseases on you that I put on the Egyptians for I am the Lord your healer.

04:40.978 --> 04:49.010
Somebody joked saying that they'd been twice to the gym already, once to join in the second time to renew their membership.

04:49.922 --> 04:58.874
My husband and I have joined a gym because everybody knows that exercise is vital for maintaining strength, flexibility, and cardiovascular health.

04:59.915 --> 05:05.783
I believe in moderation, but do try to incorporate more steps and stairs into our daily routine.

05:06.925 --> 05:10.229
Regular activity reduces the risk of chronic diseases.

05:11.010 --> 05:16.978
And in our fast-paced world, rest is often overlooked, yet it's also vital for overall health.

05:17.730 --> 05:28.426
My husband and I aim for seven to nine hours of quality sleep and try to establish a consistent sleep schedule despite interruptions from travel and jet lag.

05:29.147 --> 05:34.555
It's important to incorporate Sabbath rest days to recharge and to avoid burnout.

05:35.296 --> 05:47.634
In fact, Charlie Kirk's last word to the world before his tragic assassination was his book Stop in the Name of God, Why Honoring the Sabbath Will Transform Your Life.

05:48.706 --> 05:55.155
Yes indeed, Isaiah 5811 highlights the restorative power of following God's guidance.

05:56.077 --> 06:01.084
The Lord promises to guide you continually to be like a well-watered garden.

06:01.885 --> 06:06.432
It's also important to have a goal of cultivating joy and gratitude daily.

06:07.553 --> 06:09.757
This fosters emotional resilience.

06:10.678 --> 06:16.306
Proverbs 1722 declares, A cheerful heart is good medicine.

06:16.834 --> 06:19.317
But a crushed spirit dries up the bones.

06:20.418 --> 06:28.067
A sound mind equips us to watch especially for the rapture without being weighed down by anxiety and the cares of this world.

06:28.988 --> 06:41.041
As John the Apostle wrote in three John two, Beloved, I pray that you may prosper in all things and be in health, even as your soul prospers, amen.

06:41.061 --> 06:45.266
Well, no, I'd like to share wisdom from cardiologists alphine M. Rani

06:45.698 --> 06:53.089
Concerning our words and how words shape not merely our mood, but are the very architecture of our brains.

06:53.810 --> 07:05.348
A former teacher came to him complaining and he said he listened to her speak 11 times uttering the phrase, I just can't seem to, like I just can't seem to focus.

07:05.909 --> 07:07.131
I can't seem to remember.

07:07.932 --> 07:10.396
I can't seem to feel like myself and so forth.

07:11.157 --> 07:14.482
Dr. M. Ronnie said he was not describing her condition.

07:14.914 --> 07:16.496
She was prescribing it.

07:17.216 --> 07:23.142
Her nervous system, that obedient and literal Oregon, was doing precisely what it was told to do.

07:24.283 --> 07:32.771
You see, a word once uttered becomes an event in the body, is heard by our own ears, and literally registered as real.

07:33.732 --> 07:41.340
A single negative utterance lands with a weight that a dozen affirmations just can't counterbalance.

07:41.360 --> 07:43.762
Autoimmunity is a condition where the

07:43.842 --> 07:54.475
immune system mistakenly attacks the body's own healthy cells, tissues, and organs, rather than protecting us against foreign invaders like viruses or bacteria.

07:55.356 --> 08:03.766
Dr. M. Ronnie said, think of negativity as verbal autoimmunity, self-attacking the self through our own words.

08:04.507 --> 08:10.354
He observed that the patient who says, I'm falling apart, is in effect issuing a command

08:11.362 --> 08:16.949
You see, the body just can't distinguish metaphor from instruction, so it begins to comply.

08:16.969 --> 08:22.115
In short, we can become fluent in our own destruction if we're not careful.

08:22.716 --> 08:29.344
The phrases we often repeat can become neurological grooves, the paths of least resistance.

08:29.364 --> 08:40.818
And so the person who has said 10,000 times, I am no good at this, finds the thought as automatic as breathing, not because it's true, but because it's routine.

08:41.698 --> 08:44.862
What then can be done to fix these automatic outbursts?

08:45.723 --> 08:51.691
First, let's make a deliberate effort to notice phrases that habitually tumble out of our mouths.

08:51.711 --> 09:02.765
You may be astonished to discover how much of your daily conversation amounts to small curses, tiny prophecies of defeat, spoken casually without notice.

09:02.785 --> 09:06.770
Secondly, and this is harder, let's determine to interrupt the pattern.

09:07.266 --> 09:11.550
Let's catch the negative utterances before they cross from thought into speech.

09:12.391 --> 09:14.713
In this practice, something remarkable happens.

09:15.374 --> 09:20.539
The negative thought is denied its usual pathway and begins to loosen its grip.

09:21.680 --> 09:24.062
Unfired, the neutral circuit weakens.

09:24.543 --> 09:28.927
Starved of repetition, negativity begins to atrophy.

09:29.788 --> 09:31.549
You see, silence is not empty.

09:31.630 --> 09:33.151
It's a form of editing.

09:33.832 --> 09:36.274
It's a refusal to ratify something bad.

09:36.706 --> 09:47.441
a patient recovering from a stroke, told Dr. Imrani he felt he had been given a second chance in life, not just to communicate, but to choose his words wisely.

09:48.422 --> 10:05.426
He realized that he had been speaking carelessly all of his life, but through affliction he had stumbled upon an ancient truth that's expressed in one of my favorite Bible verses, Proverbs 1821, death and life are in the power of the tongue.

10:06.146 --> 10:16.917
This verse affirms that our words have immense power to create positive or destructive outcomes, to bring blessings or curses, healing our harm to ourselves and others.

10:17.517 --> 10:20.861
And ultimately, we experience the consequences of our speech.

10:22.042 --> 10:30.911
So this video today is a call to speak life, love, and encouragement rather than negativity, because our speech shapes our reality and relationships.

10:31.532 --> 10:34.034
Let's learn to treat our words like medicine,

10:34.722 --> 10:36.965
some words healed, in other words, poison.

10:37.626 --> 10:45.255
Dr. M. Ronnie said that we're all physicians of ourselves, and the tongue is the most potent instrument in our physician's bag.

10:45.916 --> 10:50.162
Or it can be the most dangerous, depending entirely on how we use our tongues.

10:51.664 --> 11:02.898
Meanwhile, the Harvard Medical School's Journal of Psychosomatic Research recently described how verbal suggestions and negative narratives impact our immune function.

11:03.746 --> 11:07.511
The journal also affirmed that words in mindset matter biologically.

11:08.433 --> 11:18.267
Shifting from negative self-narratives like, I'm always tired to positive ones like, I'm resting and recovering, can help support better outcomes.

11:19.028 --> 11:25.096
Although of course it's not magic, and severe health issues do still demand special attention.

11:26.438 --> 11:31.826
But if you're the type of person to constantly repeat, I feel bad, I'm exhausted, or I'm old,

11:32.450 --> 11:36.978
Science is now describing those phrases as neurobiological programming.

11:37.939 --> 11:45.112
You see, our cells don't have ears, but they have chemical receptors that pick up every signal sent by our brain.

11:46.093 --> 11:54.949
If we speak out of lack or talk about disease, we're sending a direct order to our system and our bodies are simply wired to obey our voice.

11:55.930 --> 11:58.034
Just as positive thinking can heal,

11:58.466 --> 12:05.795
Constant negative affirmations release an immediate cascade of stress hormones that work against our immune shield.

12:06.436 --> 12:12.904
Negative language is, in practice, a self-administered poison that withers vitality from within.

12:12.944 --> 12:23.538
The Harvard Journal confirmed the notion that normalizing phrases of defeat or weakness trains your nervous system to operate in a state of constant survival.

12:24.130 --> 12:28.676
Ignoring the consequences of negative words is why so many medical treatments fail.

12:29.517 --> 12:36.367
But the journal also firm that we can rewire our biological response by changing our narratives.

12:37.028 --> 12:43.136
That's why it's so important to speak the word of God constantly to initiate cellular repair functions.

12:44.438 --> 12:50.226
Well, research from Harvard University confirmed that using constructive language not only improves mood,

12:50.402 --> 12:58.391
but optimizes heart rate and strengthens inflammatory responses, demonstrating that words are biological engineering tools.

12:59.913 --> 13:03.437
So now to summarize, how do we re-program ourselves?

13:03.618 --> 13:06.821
First of all, the research says, identify the poison.

13:07.462 --> 13:11.287
Become aware of your speech habits, like saying, this is killing me.

13:11.928 --> 13:17.394
For example, I refuse to buy any food or drink in the grocery store packaged with a word death.

13:17.826 --> 13:20.889
like restaurants serving death by chocolate desserts.

13:21.750 --> 13:29.238
Next, change phrases like, I feel terrible to something like, this body of mine is working on healing.

13:30.098 --> 13:37.906
Amazingly, research has labeled the wake up window, meaning your first words of the day program your morning chemistry.

13:38.867 --> 13:45.554
So as you open your eyes, avoid complaining, which unknowingly can shoot up a spike of unnecessary cortisol.

13:46.114 --> 13:52.841
I find it interesting that upon awakening, a practicing Jew is taught immediately to offer a prayer of thanks.

13:53.802 --> 13:59.028
Their first words of the morning express gratitude to God, affirming faith in a new day.

13:59.068 --> 14:11.782
Also, determine to surround yourself with narratives and people that add vitality to your life, where research shows that even the negative words of others can affect our own internal chemistry.

14:13.023 --> 14:15.346
And stop saying, it runs in the family.

14:15.874 --> 14:19.559
The Lord has given us authority and power to break generational curses.

14:20.220 --> 14:20.540
Amen.

14:21.942 --> 14:25.768
Now, speaking of the power of the spoken word, I like to use a biblical affirmation.

14:25.968 --> 14:27.791
It is well with my soul.

14:29.052 --> 14:32.076
Your body may be well enough, but how's your soul?

14:33.018 --> 14:33.939
Is your soul well?

14:34.680 --> 14:42.871
I'd like to tell you the true story of overcoming severe hardships and the power of the spoken word behind the beloved hymn.

14:43.252 --> 14:44.754
It is well with my soul.

14:45.506 --> 14:48.529
This faith filled him was written by Horatio Spafford.

14:48.569 --> 14:54.074
He founded the American colony in Jerusalem, where we've been privileged to minister for many years.

14:54.795 --> 14:57.998
And I've seen the original handwritten text of his lyrics.

14:59.199 --> 15:04.924
In the late 19th century, Spafford was a successful lawyer living in Chicago in the United States.

15:05.805 --> 15:08.368
By all appearances, life had been generous to him.

15:09.128 --> 15:15.154
He enjoyed a thriving legal practice, a loving marriage to his wife, Anna, and they had five beautiful children.

15:15.746 --> 15:18.250
as well as a solid faith that shaped their home.

15:18.891 --> 15:21.956
Yet, their seemingly ideal world was shattered.

15:22.637 --> 15:32.051
First, in 1871, disaster struck when the great Chicago fire ravaged their city, destroying much of Spafford's real estate investments.

15:32.071 --> 15:36.919
As he struggled to recover from financial ruin, another more personal tragedy followed.

15:37.540 --> 15:41.586
The death from Scarlet Fever of his four-year-old son, Horatio Jr.

15:42.466 --> 15:48.917
grief filled their household, but the spaffards clung firmly to their faith, trusting God as their refuge in sorrow.

15:49.938 --> 16:01.137
Two years later, hoping for rest and spiritual renewal, the family planned a journey to Europe to join their close friend, the renowned evangelist Dwight Moody, for a revival tour.

16:02.178 --> 16:09.330
At the first moment, urgent business matters delayed Horatio, and he sent Anna ahead with their four daughters.

16:10.050 --> 16:13.094
But midway across the Atlantic, tragedy struck again.

16:13.715 --> 16:17.241
Their steamship collided with another vessel and sank within minutes.

16:18.202 --> 16:20.666
Only a few passengers survived.

16:20.686 --> 16:26.835
Anna was rescued unconscious on floating wreckage, but all four of their daughters were drowned.

16:27.916 --> 16:34.786
Upon arrival in Cardiff Wales, Anna sent her husband a heartbreaking telegram saying, saved alone.

16:35.968 --> 16:37.330
Well, overcome with grief,

16:37.570 --> 16:41.356
Horatio immediately boarded another ship to reunite with his bereaved wife.

16:42.377 --> 16:49.949
And as the vessel passed near where his daughters had perished, he took out a sheet of Chicago's stationery and penned these words.

16:50.870 --> 17:02.909
When peace, like a river at a tinneth my way, when sorrows like sea billows roll, whatever my lot thou hast taught me to say, it is well, it is well with my soul.

17:03.931 --> 17:06.194
Has God taught you to say it as well with your soul?

17:06.818 --> 17:11.025
Or better still, have you taught yourself to say it's well with my soul?"

17:12.066 --> 17:16.494
The ratio of Spafford was quoting 2 Kings 4, 26 in the Hebrew Bible.

17:17.255 --> 17:34.162
Words of a Shunomite woman following the tragic death of her son by faith she had the presence of mine to respond to the prophet Elisha in his well because her faith was not diminished and her son was raised from the dead by Elisha's prayers.

17:35.010 --> 17:39.394
spaffords him as a profound declaration of faith born in the depths of anguish.

17:40.035 --> 17:45.320
It's a testimony to unwavering trust in God in the middle of life's fiercest storms.

17:46.221 --> 17:54.669
Out of their brokenness, Horatio and Anna, decided to move to Jerusalem to watch Bible prophecy unfold and to pray.

17:55.430 --> 18:01.416
And there they opened the famous American colony, both as a Christian community, hospital, and house a prayer.

18:02.237 --> 18:03.538
Today it's a Swiss

18:03.650 --> 18:10.981
run boutique hotel whereby the grace of God our ministry has continued their work of prayer for all of the peoples of the region.

18:11.642 --> 18:22.197
Spafford's time was hymn has brought comfort to millions reminding us that even when everything around us is dark and desperate divine peace is available to steady our souls.

18:23.059 --> 18:30.770
I particularly appreciate the two closing stanzas of Spafford's hymn because he possessed revelation about the rapture.

18:31.522 --> 18:40.492
The penultimate stanza goes like this, Lord, his for thee, for thy coming we wait, the sky, not the grave is our goal.

18:41.393 --> 18:46.800
O Trump of the angel, O voice of the Lord, blessed hope, blessed rest of my soul.

18:47.540 --> 18:49.923
Those are the words of a real man of God.

18:50.584 --> 18:53.467
He unashamedly looked forward to the rapture.

18:54.148 --> 18:55.890
How many preachers can say that today?

18:56.322 --> 19:01.727
Unfortunately, many preachers tragically are denying the rapture at a time when it's very imminent.

19:02.888 --> 19:11.677
But in his hymn, Spafford quoted, Titus 2, 13, Our Blessed Hope, the appearing of the glory of a great God and Savior, Jesus the Messiah.

19:12.758 --> 19:24.850
And the final stanza goes like this, And Lord, hasteth the day when faith shall be sight, The clouds be rolled back as a scroll, The trump shall resound, and the Lord shall descend,

19:25.186 --> 19:27.629
A song in the night, oh, my soul.

19:28.751 --> 19:38.405
That stanza put into poetry, 1 Corinthians 1552, which declares that we shall be changed in a flash in the triggering of an eye at the last trumpet.

19:39.186 --> 19:46.216
For the trump will sound, the dead will be raised incorruptible, and we shall be changed."

19:46.236 --> 19:51.403
Well, my friend, no matter what this week has brought, choose my faith to rejoice in the goodness of the Lord.

19:51.844 --> 19:53.586
Rejoicing is an act of faith.

19:54.178 --> 19:57.101
Rejoicing puts an immediate stop to stress.

19:58.302 --> 20:05.208
You see, when we praise God, He honors our faith, doors open, our strength is renewed, and our hope rises again.

20:05.248 --> 20:16.379
One of the most powerful passages for our health is found in Psalm 103, which proclaims, blessed the Lord, O my soul, and forget not all His benefits.

20:17.139 --> 20:19.382
So what is the Lord's benefit package?

20:19.402 --> 20:24.146
The Psalm says, He forgives all of our iniquities and heals all of our diseases.

20:24.834 --> 20:28.159
God's blessings include both forgiveness and physical healing.

20:28.579 --> 20:31.002
But notice that forgiveness is mentioned first.

20:31.763 --> 20:37.351
It's important to ask for forgiveness on a regular basis and to keep a clean conscience before God.

20:37.892 --> 20:43.580
Then we can boldly approach the Lord's throne by faith to make a request known to Him with thanksgiving.

20:44.481 --> 20:47.805
And God promises to renew our strength like the eagles.

20:49.408 --> 20:54.194
As we await the coming of the Lord, I want to share a powerful key to supernatural strength.

20:54.882 --> 21:00.108
From time to time, I try to encourage myself with the example of the man of God, A.

21:00.429 --> 21:04.233
B. Simpson, who was founder of the Christian and Missionary Alliance.

21:05.215 --> 21:12.544
After a long sickness, Simpson learned to live supernaturally by drawing strength from the Lord's indwelling presence.

21:13.425 --> 21:24.178
This revelation caused him to shift from self-effort to moment by moment dependence on the Lord within as his constant supply of life, healing, and power.

21:24.834 --> 21:31.643
after his own miraculous recovery from a severe heart condition, Simpson vowed to trust God fully for his health.

21:32.264 --> 21:33.926
And that's what we are doing today.

21:34.287 --> 21:36.129
You and I are trusting God for our health.

21:37.131 --> 21:48.286
From that time forward, Simpson drew supernatural vitality from the Lord's indwelling presence, enabling vigorous ministry despite a past history of being frail.

21:49.127 --> 21:50.910
What a revelation, what a change.

21:51.590 --> 21:54.194
Simpson taught and practiced this deeper life

21:54.594 --> 21:58.760
applying the Lord's fullness to spirit, soul, body, mind, and will.

21:59.702 --> 22:09.477
Overcoming exhaustion, temptations, and physical weaknesses, not somehow through stored-up faith, but by literally breathing in the Lord's life afresh.

22:10.418 --> 22:18.671
The result was sustained service, including the ability to open missions, healing homes, and educational institutions that reached thousands.

22:19.332 --> 22:23.058
In essence, Simpson's supernatural existence stemmed from

22:23.298 --> 22:27.185
appropriating Colossians 1, 27 in the New Testament.

22:27.545 --> 22:31.191
That first declares Christ in you the hope of glory.

22:31.712 --> 22:33.135
And that was the secret of power.

22:33.936 --> 22:36.140
Now, that's not poetic language.

22:36.160 --> 22:37.162
It's not a metaphor.

22:37.182 --> 22:46.898
It's to be believed literally that the risen Lord Jesus comes when we're born again to live inside us, inside consecrated believers.

22:47.554 --> 22:48.335
So A.B.

22:48.395 --> 22:54.581
Simpson was greatly blessed to discover how to yield entirely to the Lord's inner presence for all of his needs.

22:55.222 --> 23:02.350
He learned to glorify God through a life of effortless rest and divine enablement rather than human striving.

23:03.090 --> 23:10.538
This approach of living by the faith of the Son of God not only healed his body but empowered his global evangelistic efforts.

23:11.219 --> 23:14.002
True strength flows from union with arisen Lord.

23:14.274 --> 23:19.420
flowing and flooding away disease and infirmity with the Lord's perfect life.

23:20.982 --> 23:25.768
Now then we also have to learn to keep up our emotional strength and not allow it to be drained.

23:26.689 --> 23:44.210
A friend asked me for example how I would handle aggressive or argumentative persons on social media and I replied that my general rule on engaging with argumentative souls is usually I allow somebody to contradict me twice and I attempt to answer them politely twice

23:44.546 --> 23:48.891
But if they continue aggressively, then it's three strikes and they're out.

23:49.592 --> 23:53.456
That's my rule to maintain my sanity, my time and my energy.

23:54.037 --> 23:57.741
After all, some people are not teachable and only want to argue.

23:57.881 --> 24:00.684
So we have to know by the spirit whom to answer.

24:01.625 --> 24:04.689
Let's teach our children and grandchildren in the meantime to pray.

24:05.409 --> 24:09.895
Should the Lord Terry, we may not be around for their entire lives, but God will.

24:10.575 --> 24:12.978
Children also need the supernatural power of God.

24:13.378 --> 24:18.306
The enemy has a plan for the last days, lies, confusion, depression, death and destruction.

24:18.867 --> 24:21.091
It's clear the enemy is after our children.

24:21.712 --> 24:24.076
They face situations we never had to face.

24:24.837 --> 24:28.844
If there ever was a generation that needs the power of God, it's this generation.

24:29.585 --> 24:34.513
God foresaw the technological age and the dangers of artificial intelligence.

24:34.534 --> 24:39.602
Thankfully, God's plan for the last days is a mighty outpouring of His Holy Spirit.

24:40.194 --> 24:44.959
You see, the Bible promises your sons and your daughters shall prophesy and see visions.

24:46.160 --> 24:51.145
So with all the upheaval going on in this world, you may be asking yourself, what is this world coming to?

24:51.185 --> 24:58.313
And my answer to you is exactly what Jesus said it would be when he described the end time birth pains.

24:58.913 --> 25:00.375
That means he is coming soon.

25:01.135 --> 25:05.160
So today, do something positive for which your future self will be grateful.

25:05.820 --> 25:07.602
Practice portion control.

25:08.066 --> 25:18.276
consciously speak positive affirmations of faith, and most of all, receive the Savior of the universe into your heart so you can draw from His holy power.

25:19.458 --> 25:20.999
May I ask, do you know the Lord?

25:21.099 --> 25:22.681
Jesus has Messiah and Savior.

25:23.442 --> 25:26.665
No other God bled for us, no other God came to save us.

25:27.005 --> 25:29.488
Jesus, Yeshua is His Hebrew name.

25:30.249 --> 25:33.552
He alone heals us from the curse of eternal death.

25:34.092 --> 25:35.634
There's salvation and no other,

25:36.162 --> 25:41.590
He alone died for our sins as our mediator before God, and He was raised from the dead.

25:42.292 --> 25:44.255
He was foretold by the Hebrew prophets.

25:44.856 --> 25:47.540
He alone is the way, the truth, and the life of God.

25:48.241 --> 25:54.290
He invites all of us to come to Him, to escape the terrible judgments cataloged in the book of Revelation.

25:55.352 --> 26:04.466
So if you've not yet confessed Jesus as Lord, I urge you to call in His name and believe that He is the Son of God who died for our sins and rose from the dead.

26:04.834 --> 26:11.102
And then the Bible promises, you shall be saved and you'll be ready for the soon and sudden appearing of the Lord.

26:11.583 --> 26:13.065
That's our blessed hope.

26:13.466 --> 26:13.786
Amen.

26:14.968 --> 26:20.015
